A LOT of us admittedly can’t live without our cellphones. In fact, most of us have our entire lives on that little gadget. While a cellphone can be used for a variety of things, many relationship experts agree that it is one of the breeding grounds for cheating. According to the global average usage, many of us spend five to nine hours daily on our cellphones, which can promote infidelity. With online dating surging since Covid-19, many have taken the opportunity to cheat in their relationships. So, how do you know that your partner is cheating using their cellphones? Her
 Norm magazine gives some red flags to look out for: 1. They Suddenly Become Overprotective About Their Phones If your partner starts to use their phone more often than usual, then it’s time to ring the alarm like Beyonce. If there is nothing to hide, then they will not become uncomfortable over a mere call or texts. 2. They Have Strange Names On Their Contact List The use of an alias name during cheating is very popular. According to experts, many of these names are hidden behind unpopular alphabet letters such us X, Y, Z and Q. 3. No History of Calls or Texts This is a really common thing that cheaters tend to do. While they may think it will cover their tracks because there is no trail of unfaithfulness, they don’t realise that if you delete all your calls and texts, it looks odd. 4. They Now Take Their Calls Outside Of course, there is a certain amount of space you want when taking a call. Privacy is important when you’re on the phone and everyone understands that. However, if your partner has suddenly started taking their calls outside the house, this is concerning. 5. They Have More Than Two Phones Many people have a separate phone for work, social or private lives. However, when one has more than three phones and can’t explain why, this becomes a serious red flag.